00:08:47.640 --> 00:08:49.720
I come back to the
same point that I

00:08:49.720 --> 00:08:51.790
have reached my
equilibrium again.

00:08:51.790 --> 00:08:55.200
I have done a cyclic process.

00:08:55.200 --> 00:08:59.550
Now at each stage of this
cyclic process presumably

00:08:59.550 --> 00:09:02.990
the system takes in a
certain amount of heat.

00:09:02.990 --> 00:09:06.910
So let's say that
there is a dQ that

00:09:06.910 --> 00:09:09.860
goes at this stage
of the process.

00:09:09.860 --> 00:09:14.030
So I use s to indicate, say,
stage 0, one, two, three,

00:09:14.030 --> 00:09:16.110
four all the way coming back.

00:09:16.110 --> 00:09:19.890
So this is just a
numbering process.

00:09:19.890 --> 00:09:22.570
The statement of
Clausius's theorem

00:09:22.570 --> 00:09:29.220
is that for any cyclic process
if I go out around the cycle,

00:09:29.220 --> 00:09:33.030
add up these elements of
heat that are delivered

00:09:33.030 --> 00:09:37.660
