00:27:55.480 --> 00:27:58.720
now I've added S.
How many things

00:27:58.720 --> 00:28:01.920
do I need to describe the
system in equilibrium?

00:28:01.920 --> 00:28:05.100
A lot of these are
dependent on each other.

00:28:05.100 --> 00:28:07.490
And in particular
saw that mechanically

00:28:07.490 --> 00:28:11.250
if there was the only thing
that was happening in the story,

00:28:11.250 --> 00:28:14.440
J's could be obtained from
the derivatives of energy

00:28:14.440 --> 00:28:16.390
with respect to x.

00:28:16.390 --> 00:28:20.550
So J's, in some sense, once
you had E were given to you.

00:28:20.550 --> 00:28:22.290
You didn't have to
list all of the J's.

00:28:22.290 --> 00:28:26.650
You just needed to add
E as a function of x's.

00:28:26.650 --> 00:28:30.120
But when you have thermal
transformations around,

00:28:30.120 --> 00:28:31.540
that's not enough.

00:28:31.540 --> 00:28:36.030
This equation says that if
there are n ways of doing work

00:28:36.030 --> 00:28:40.130
on the system, there is
one of the doing heat.

00:28:40.130 --> 00:28:44.590
You have n plus 1 independent
degrees of freedom..

00:28:44.590 --> 00:28:54.320
So n ways of sum over i,
Ji, dxi, one way of SdT,

00:28:54.320 --> 00:29:04.420
you have n plus one
independent variables

00:29:04.420 --> 00:29:05.580
to describe your system.

00:29:12.920 --> 00:29:17.000
And once you realize
that you have

00:29:17.000 --> 00:29:20.160
a certain amount of freedom
in choosing precisely

00:29:20.160 --> 00:29:23.060
which n plus one
you want to select.

00:29:23.060 --> 00:29:31.810
So I could select all of
the x's and one temperature.

00:29:31.810 --> 00:29:35.270
I could select all of
the J's and one energy.

00:29:35.270 --> 00:29:37.870
So I have a number of choices.

00:29:37.870 --> 00:29:42.140
And once I have made my
choice I can rearrange things

00:29:42.140 --> 00:29:43.000
accordingly.

00:29:43.000 --> 00:29:46.750
So suppose I had chosen
the energy in xi,

00:29:46.750 --> 00:29:54.870
then I could write dS to
be dE over T minus sum

00:29:54.870 --> 00:29:59.200
over i Ji over T xi.

00:29:59.200 --> 00:30:04.166
So I just rearrange this
expression and solve for dS.

00:30:04.166 --> 00:30:07.650
So this amounts to
my having chosen

00:30:07.650 --> 00:30:13.710
x's and E's as independent
variables and prescribed

00:30:13.710 --> 00:30:20.820
through this important law s
as a function of E and x's.

00:30:20.820 --> 00:30:22.540
What about everything else?

00:30:22.540 --> 00:30:25.970
Well, everything else you
can calculate by derivatives.

00:30:25.970 --> 00:30:31.740
So 1 over T would be
dS by dE at constant x.

00:30:31.740 --> 00:30:44.000
While Ji over T would be minus
dS by dxi at constant E and xJ

00:30:44.000 --> 00:30:45.362
that is not equal to i.

00:30:53.298 --> 00:30:55.290
OK?

00:30:55.290 --> 00:30:55.920
Fine.

00:30:55.920 --> 00:31:00.810
So that's sort of
kind of extract

00:31:00.810 --> 00:31:06.690
the mathematical content that
we can get out of the second law

00:31:06.690 --> 00:31:09.020
through this Clausius's theorem.

00:31:09.020 --> 00:31:12.730
There is one important
corollary that

00:31:12.730 --> 00:31:16.210
has to do be irreversible
transformations.

00:31:24.220 --> 00:31:29.180
After all, in setting up
the Clausius's theorem

00:31:29.180 --> 00:31:33.080
I did not say anything
about the necessity

00:31:33.080 --> 00:31:38.140
of being in equilibrium in
order to achieve the inequality.

00:31:38.140 --> 00:31:42.340
Reversibility allowed me
to get it as an equality.

00:31:42.340 --> 00:31:44.010
So what can I do?

00:31:44.010 --> 00:31:47.950
I can take any
complicated space.

00:31:47.950 --> 00:31:54.340
I can pick a point
A and in principle,

00:31:54.340 --> 00:31:59.690
make an irreversible
transformation to some point B.

00:31:59.690 --> 00:32:02.860
And maybe in that
process I will get

00:32:02.860 --> 00:32:05.940
some heat inputted
through the system dQ.

00:32:08.590 --> 00:32:18.310
And what I would have is that
the integral going from A to B,

00:32:18.310 --> 00:32:28.550
dQ divided by T along the path
that I have described here

00:32:28.550 --> 00:32:31.830
which is irreversible.

00:32:31.830 --> 00:32:34.960
But I can't say anything
about it at this point.

00:32:34.960 --> 00:32:38.560
Clausius's theorem
has to do with cycles.

00:32:38.560 --> 00:32:45.470
So I can, in principle connect
back from B to A reversibly.

00:32:45.470 --> 00:32:55.920
So I go integral from B to
A, dQ reversible over T.

00:32:55.920 --> 00:33:00.310
And having completed the
cycle I know for this cycle

00:33:00.310 --> 00:33:02.020
that this is negative.

00:33:05.190 --> 00:33:10.470
If I were to take this to the
other side of the equation

00:33:10.470 --> 00:33:15.240
it becomes essentially the
difference of the entropies,

00:33:15.240 --> 00:33:17.850
or here it's also the
difference of entropies.

00:33:17.850 --> 00:33:20.530
But I prefer it to
be on the other side.

00:33:20.530 --> 00:33:23.470
And then to make
these two points very

00:33:23.470 --> 00:33:26.310
close to each other,
in which case,

00:33:26.310 --> 00:33:33.747
I can write that dQ is
less than or equal to TdS.

00:33:39.400 --> 00:33:46.230
This is the change in entropy
in going from A to B. OK?

00:33:46.230 --> 00:33:51.530
Again, there's some question
here as to what this T is.

00:33:51.530 --> 00:33:55.170
So let's get rid
of that uncertainty

00:33:55.170 --> 00:33:57.470
by looking at processes
that are adiabatic.

00:34:02.410 --> 00:34:04.800
So I make sure that
there is no heat

00:34:04.800 --> 00:34:10.639
exchange in going from A to
B. What do I conclude then?

00:34:10.639 --> 00:34:14.560
Is that for these processes
the change in entropy

00:34:14.560 --> 00:34:15.380
has to be positive.

00:34:18.121 --> 00:34:18.620
OK?

00:34:18.620 --> 00:34:22.900
Because T's are generally
positive quantities.

00:34:22.900 --> 00:34:24.370
OK?

00:34:24.370 --> 00:34:28.280
So a consequence of
Clausius's theorem

00:34:28.280 --> 00:34:33.730
is that entropy can only
increase in any transformation.

00:34:33.730 --> 00:34:37.080
Its change in entropy would
be 0 for these adiabatic

00:34:37.080 --> 00:34:44.360
transformations if you
have reversible processes.

00:34:46.989 --> 00:34:49.630
So this is actually another
one of those statements

00:34:49.630 --> 00:34:51.480
that you have to
think a little bit

00:34:51.480 --> 00:34:55.480
to see whether it
has any use or not.

00:34:55.480 --> 00:35:00.250
Because we all say that
entropy has to increase,

00:35:00.250 --> 00:35:02.670
but is that what we
have proven here?

00:35:02.670 --> 00:35:04.080
Not quite.

00:35:04.080 --> 00:35:09.900
Because what we've proven is
that if you have a system that

00:35:09.900 --> 00:35:16.090
is isolated, so there is
a system that is isolated

