work remained.

01:01:16.340 --> 01:01:18.840
I could do it the
other way around.

01:01:18.840 --> 01:01:23.230
I can define a function
that is obtained

01:01:23.230 --> 01:01:31.150
by subtracting from the
energy the chemical work,

01:01:31.150 --> 01:01:38.720
but leaving the mechanical
component aside.

01:01:38.720 --> 01:01:45.940
So this function dG, OK, I
should go one step before.

01:01:45.940 --> 01:01:52.310
So once we separate out
the contributions of Jidxi

01:01:52.310 --> 01:01:55.790
into mechanical and
chemical components,

01:01:55.790 --> 01:02:02.800
I would write dE as TdS
plus sum over iJidxi,

01:02:02.800 --> 01:02:07.159
plus sum over alpha
mu alpha dN alpha.

01:02:07.159 --> 01:02:08.550
OK?

01:02:08.550 --> 01:02:13.900
I just explicitly separating
out those two sources of work.

01:02:13.900 --> 01:02:18.840
Now when I constructed G,
which subtracts from e, the mu,

01:02:18.840 --> 01:02:20.870
but not the J, what happens?

01:02:20.870 --> 01:02:24.160
I will get a minus TdS.

01:02:24.160 --> 01:02:25.595
This will remain unchanged.

01:02:28.290 --> 01:02:33.230
This will get transformed
to N alpha, d mu alpha.

01:02:36.400 --> 01:02:37.430
Just hold on a second.

01:02:37.430 --> 01:02:43.870
So this entity that is called
the grand potential actually

01:02:43.870 --> 01:02:47.340
completes the list of
these functions of state

01:02:47.340 --> 01:03:00.820
that I wanted to
tell you is naturally

01:03:00.820 --> 01:03:06.050
a function of T, the
chemical potentials

01:03:06.050 --> 01:03:07.900
as well as the displacement.

01:03:07.900 --> 01:03:10.230
For example, if it's a
gas the displacements

01:03:10.230 --> 01:03:12.470
will include the
volume which tell you

01:03:12.470 --> 01:03:14.000
how much material you have.

01:03:14.000 --> 01:03:14.882
Yes?

01:03:14.882 --> 01:03:16.340
AUDIENCE: In that
