01:10:02.430 --> 01:10:06.020
One set of statement
follow from the discussion

01:10:06.020 --> 01:10:09.095
that we have had so far, which
has to do with extensivity.

01:10:14.190 --> 01:10:15.570
What do I mean?

01:10:15.570 --> 01:10:21.060
Let's take a look at our most
fundamental expression, which

01:10:21.060 --> 01:10:30.150
is dE is TdS plus
sum over iJdxi,

01:10:30.150 --> 01:10:34.517
plus sum over alpha
mu alpha dN alpha.

01:10:37.720 --> 01:10:46.420
Now you recognize that certainly
as the amount of material

01:10:46.420 --> 01:10:50.020
gets increased, the number
of particles increases.

01:10:50.020 --> 01:10:53.400
The typical sizes and
displacements get bigger.

01:10:53.400 --> 01:10:55.750
The energy content gets bigger.

01:10:55.750 --> 01:10:58.915
The entropy content is
related to the heat content

01:10:58.915 --> 01:11:00.910
and so that gets bigger.

01:11:00.910 --> 01:11:06.490
So these differential forms
that I have on this expression,

01:11:06.490 --> 01:11:10.430
they're all proportional
to the size of the system.

01:11:10.430 --> 01:11:12.060
What does that mean?

01:11:12.060 --> 01:11:14.700
It means that e, the
way that I have it

01:11:14.700 --> 01:11:22.480
here has as its natural
variables S, x, N.

01:11:22.480 --> 01:11:27.790
And extensivity means that if I
were to make my system twice as

01:11:27.790 --> 01:11:31.710
large, so that all
of these quantities

01:11:31.710 --> 01:11:34.460
would get multiplied
by a factor of two,

01:11:34.460 --> 01:11:38.187
the energy content would get
multiplied by a factor of two.

01:11:43.660 --> 01:11:46.420
OK?

01:11:46.420 --> 01:11:53.592
Now it is important to state
that this is not a requirement.

01:11:53.592 --> 01:11:54.092
OK?

